The Christian Association of Nigeria, Ijebu East Local Government Area chapter, has organised a thanksgiving and prayer service. The annual programme, according to a statement on Sunday, afforded the people an opportunity to pray for the peace of the local government, state and the country. It was hosted by the Chairman of Ogun State Television, Mr Olatunde Oladunjoye. Special prayers were said for the Governor of Ogun State, Mr. Dapo Abiodun; and the Awujale of Ijebuland, Oba Sikiru Adetona, according to the statement. “Close to a thousand delegates and chieftains of the All Progressives Congress from the 11 wards that make up the local government attended the event. They were led in prayers by over 60 clergymen from various denominations. “The event, which was organised under the auspices of the Christian Association of Nigeria, Ijebu East Local Government Area chapter, was to thank God for his faithfulness over Ijebu East Local Government Area, Ogun State and Nigeria.”